    <p>
        - Properties of hydrocarbons depend on the size of their molecules.<br>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Boiling Point</b>: Temperature at which the liquid boils 
                or the gas condenses. Bigger size = higher boiling point.</li>
            <li><b>Volatility</b>: The tendency to turn into a gas. Bigger size = lower volatility.</li>
            <li><b>Viscosity</b>: How easily it flows. Bigger size = higher viscosity (thicker).</li>
            <li><b>Flammability</b>: How easily it burns. Bigger size = lower flammability.</li>
        </ul>
